      "content": "# Industry Economics and Market Structure\n\n- 자동 생성 리서치 노트\n- 생성 시각: `2026-04-07T08:51:38.542014+00:00`\n- 저장 경로: `research/auto/industry-economics.md`\n- 선정 이유: target 5 docs 대비 현재 1 docs\n- 검색 쿼리: site:ifhaonline.org horse racing annual report wagering turnover, site:equibase.com horse racing fact book handle attendance, site:jockeyclub.com horse racing economic impact wagering\n\n## 수집 소스\n\n1. [2026 Fact Book - The Jockey Club](http://jockeyclub.com/factbook.asp) (duckduckgo, query=`horse racing fact book handle attendance`)\n   - snippet: Pari-Mutuel Handle Racing Statistics by Foaling Area Size of Field and Starts Per Horse Percent Starters and Winners by Age 2-Year-Old Racing Trends in U.S. Races, Purses and Foal Crops SALES Auction Sales in North America Average/Median Price Per Yearling Foal Crop/Auction Yearling Percentage Thoroughbred Racing and Breeding Worldwide ...\n   - extracted: 2026 Fact Book The Jockey Club is pleased to introduce the 2026 edition of our annual guide to the Thoroughbred industry in North America. We hope you find the statistics and information contained herein helpful in your research. Although most statistics may be considered final, some are not. For example, data pertaining to 2025 racing, supplied by racetracks of North America and the North Amer...\n2. [Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation](https://khrc.ky.gov/new_docs.aspx?cat=76&menuid=80) (duckduckgo, query=`horse racing annual report wagering turnover`)\n   - snippet: The latest on Pari-Mutuel Wagering : Current Pari-Mutuel Wagering Report The latest on Sports Wagering : Current Sports Wagering Report Use the categories below to find archived reports released by the Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation.\n   - extracted: # KENTUCKY HORSE RACING AND GAMING CORPORATION * [KHRG](https://khrc.ky.gov/) * [|](https://khrc.ky.gov/new_docs.aspx?cat=76&menuid=80) * [Office of Charitable Gaming](https://dcg.ky.gov/) * [|](https://khrc.ky.gov/new_docs.aspx?cat=76&menuid=80) * [Open Records](https://khrc.ky.gov/NewOpenRecords.aspx) [![Image 3: Official Team Kentucky logo showing outline of the state and the words Team Kent...\n3. [PDF Econ Analysis (Draft) - NYTHA](https://nytha.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-of-Racing.pdf) (duckduckgo, query=`horse racing economic impact wagering`)\n   - snippet: The State of Thoroughbred Horse Racing in the United States: An Economic Analysis and the Path to Industry Stability The sport of thoroughbred horse racing was once the most popular sport in the United States. Although large events like the Kentucky Derby and the Belmont Stakes still capture popular interest, the sport has on most days been reduced to a niche market, albeit with a highly ...\n   - extracted: > 1 ## The State of Thoroughbred Horse Racing in the United States: An Economic ## Analysis and the Path to Industry Stability The sport of thoroughbred horse racing was once the most popular sport in the United States. Although large events like the Kentucky Derby and the Belmont Stakes still capture popular interest, the sport has on most days been reduced to a niche market, albeit with a hig...\n\n## 초안 인사이트\n\n### Source 1: 2026 Fact Book - The Jockey Club\n\n2026 Fact Book The Jockey Club is pleased to introduce the 2026 edition of our annual guide to the Thoroughbred industry in North America. We hope you find the statistics and information contained herein helpful in your research. Although most statistics may be considered final, some are not. For example, data pertaining to 2025 racing, supplied by racetracks of North America and the North American Thoroughbred industry's Official database for racing information, Equibase Company, can be considered final but is subject to revision if additional data becomes available. Because of the cyclical nature of reporting procedures, however, breeding statistics such as the distribution of foals, stallions and mares are subject to change. These statistics are updated daily. (Unless otherwise noted, Canadian dollars have not been converted to U.S. dollars.) If you need additional information about the Thoroughbred breeding or racing industry, please contact our [Communications Department.](http...\n\n### Source 2: Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation\n\n# KENTUCKY HORSE RACING AND GAMING CORPORATION * [KHRG](https://khrc.ky.gov/) * [|](https://khrc.ky.gov/new_docs.aspx?cat=76&menuid=80) * [Office of Charitable Gaming](https://dcg.ky.gov/) * [|](https://khrc.ky.gov/new_docs.aspx?cat=76&menuid=80) * [Open Records](https://khrc.ky.gov/NewOpenRecords.aspx) [![Image 3: Official Team Kentucky logo showing outline of the state and the words Team Kentucky.](https://khrc.ky.gov/images/TeamKentucky_white.png)](https://kentucky.gov/Pages/home.aspx) ![Image 4](https://khrc.ky.gov/images/khrc_main.png) [![Image 5: Official KHRG logo showing the letters KHRG, with the words Kentucky Horse Racing & Gaming underneath.](https://khrc.ky.gov/images/Team_ky_khrc.png)](https://khrc.ky.gov/New_Default.aspx) KENTUCKY HORSE RACING AND GAMING CORPORATION * [Equine Health](https://khrc.ky.gov/new_docs.aspx?cat=30&menuid=30) * [Racing Licensing](https://khrc.ky.gov/Newstatic_info.aspx?static_id=554&menuid=31) * [Funds](https://khrc.ky.gov/newstatic_info.aspx...\n\n### Source 3: PDF Econ Analysis (Draft) - NYTHA\n\n> 1 ## The State of Thoroughbred Horse Racing in the United States: An Economic ## Analysis and the Path to Industry Stability The sport of thoroughbred horse racing was once the most popular sport in the United States. Although large events like the Kentucky Derby and the Belmont Stakes still capture popular interest, the sport has on most days been reduced to a niche market, albeit with a highly interested core audience. In this research paper, we study recent macroeconomic trends as well as microeco nomic decisions that have shaped the sport’s economic structure. The paper’s primary objective is to take a snapshot of the current state of the sport based on 2022 data, and to provide analysis by comparing this data with the same data from the past 20 ye ars, beginning in 2003. By examining these data points and applying simple economic principles (e.g., supply and demand, perfect competition vs . oligopoly/monopolistic markets), we aim to identify and understand the sport’s prevail...\n",
